										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p>There are many shortcuts in Blender that use numpads. Mostly keyboards on the laptop do not have a numpad. And so when I try to hit shortcuts such as Num 7 for a top view. It does not work. </p>



<span id="more-426"></span>



<p>Hopefully, there is a solution to that. <br>There is a setting under user preferences that can help called <strong>Emulate Numpad </strong> once you tick that you can use the number keys right above your number pad to use the shortcuts. </p>



<p>See the following screenshot to find where the options exists. <br>File &gt; User Preferences &gt; Input Tab </p>



